@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@apiUrl = {{baseUrl}}/api/v1

### Login as Ivan
# @name loginIvan
POST {{apiUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "ivan@example.com",
  "password": "Student123!"
}

### Login as Olena
# @name loginOlena
POST {{apiUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "olena@example.com",
  "password": "Student123!"
}

### 401: no token
GET {{apiUrl}}/reports

### 401: invalid token
GET {{apiUrl}}/reports
Authorization: Bearer invalid-token

### 200: Ivan reads own report
GET {{apiUrl}}/reports/1
Authorization: Bearer {{loginIvan.response.body.$.token}}

### 403 IDOR: Ivan tries to read Olena's report
GET {{apiUrl}}/reports/3
Authorization: Bearer {{loginIvan.response.body.$.token}}

### 403 IDOR: Ivan tries to update Olena's report
PUT {{apiUrl}}/reports/3
Authorization: Bearer {{loginIvan.response.body.$.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Blocked IDOR update"
}

### Safe SQLi: payload is treated as text and returns an empty data array
GET {{apiUrl}}/reports/demo/safe-search?title=%27%20OR%201%3D1%20--
Authorization: Bearer {{loginIvan.response.body.$.token}}

### Unsafe SQLi PoC: only works when ENABLE_UNSAFE_SQL_DEMO=true
GET {{apiUrl}}/reports/demo/unsafe-search?title=%27%20OR%201%3D1%20--
Authorization: Bearer {{loginIvan.response.body.$.token}}

### Stored XSS payload: safely rendered by frontend through textContent
POST {{apiUrl}}/reports
Authorization: Bearer {{loginIvan.response.body.$.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": 2,
  "categoryId": 1,
  "title": "<script>alert(1)</script>",
  "severity": "High",
  "description": "<img src=x onerror=alert(1)>",
  "reporter": "Security student"
}

### Security headers and health
GET {{baseUrl}}/health
Origin: http://localhost:5173
